{
  "texts": [
    "By adding more hidden layers to CNN, the recognition accuracy and performance of deep neural networks can be enhanced (Szegedy et al. 2015), but it can lead to many issues.",
    "On the one hand, as the number of network layers rises, the network must learn more parameters, which easily leads to the model being overfitted to the training data set.",
    "On the Page 19 of 43 99",
    "other hand, networks with extra layers require robust hardware resources in order to maintain the required processing power.",
    "In order to overcome these problems, the research team at Google developed the concept of inception (Al Husaini et al. 2022), which aims to build the underlying neurons and a network topology for sparse high-performance computing."
  ]
}